annotation.TEXT: I totally almost bit it there, but I was able to retreat just in time!
Fortunately, a single Podoboo bounce was all I needed, though it felt like I barely made that jump.
Yeah, nuts to you, elite pink ranger!
That felt kind of tight...

It's almost like something out of a Mega Man game or something (with a red angry face added). Also, the map music sped up and got slightly louder. (And I noticed that the music restarted when the save prompt disappeared for some reason.)
Hiyah! Made it! ...Oh, am I done with this part? Is it true final boss time?
Oh, the music changed to something nice and calm. Maybe that means I'm just about done with this level...
I guess I'll chow down before the fight, and I'll eat the popsicle after the doughnut, because that's more likely to be useful than fireballs.
BGM: Mega Man 2 - Wily Castle 1 and 2 - Okkusenman
Oh, geez. This Blatzy/Gordo combo is even trickier...
...Or, maybe it means that I'm approaching a boss, for some reason...
Aww... The game really wants to keep me small here.
Hello, and welcome back to Something else! I hope you're all having a good 4th of July today! Alright, let's take on what looks to perhaps be quite possibly the last level in the game!

That unlocked Else Castle 2 (and the music restarted after the save prompt disappeared again). So, Else Castle 2 is what I'll be doing next time, obviously! (Well, after I show the messed-up-by-WMM footage in its unmessed-up state, of course.)
There's also Gordos and firebars, obviously things that I don't want to touch.

Whoa! For some reason, I was kind of anticipating having to react like that (I checked back later, and if you don't disembark right here, you hit a wall, get knocked off the platform, and fall to your doom). Ooh, cake!
The exploding guys are fireproof.
Oh, it actually looks like these platforms are spelling out something else.
Whoa, what? Oh, man... I guess we're not done with this hack yet!
Alright, let's quickly slip past this ludicrous speed firebar here...
Whoa, man. More tricky Blatzy and Gordo shenanigans.
Okay, I've just passed the 8 minute mark of the video. Will the annotation editor's save function break after this one?
Bye! (Bone-throwing Dry Bones don't turn around at the edges of ledges.)
More Blatzies, more Gordos, and more dodging them all.
BGM: Mega Man 2 - Boss Battle
...Sigh... Well, there's one more point when I do another series of slow-motion instant replays for a similarly avoided burn. Maybe the video will correct itself there...
Oh, man. That skull box is chucking out high speed maces, just like in the level Vile Vine, I think. Wait... Are there faces on those maces?
That doughnut is nice, but is anything around here flammable or inflammable? ...I doubt it.
At least the Gordos weren't a problem to get past.
Whoa. I briefly contemplated trying to kill that one, but I quickly changed my mind about that! Also, we have random bullets now, but that's not so bad.
"Tick." Graze +1.
I think this firebar clock needs to be fixed, since it's running backwards instead of forwards here. Also, remember to adjust it for Daylight Saving Time.
So, what nasty surprises await me here, in this pouring rain?
More caffeinated firebars here, but they're not really that tricky to avoid.

Umm... Well, sort of... You guys briefly saw where I ducked under a Birdo's fireball that looked like it should've scorched Luigi's hat a couple of times there, but then the video kept cutting back to that earlier part. Then, it appeared to have fixed itself, but a small portion of the footage wasn't shown. I'll show what wasn't shown in the next episode.
Yeah, I'm not sticking around here, for obvious reasons.
Oh, man. How ominous. At least there's a light switch right above me at the start (which I almost didn't notice). Also, the game forced me to become small upon entering this level, it seems.
Huh, that seems like a rather abrupt end, but you're welcome!
Whoa! Okay, these hyperspeed-fireballing guys are back, and actually look like Birdo this time! ...Ha! I knocked his block off with that block!
Ah, these Chucks are actually punting light bulbs here. They must be getting a bunch of bright ideas all of a sudden. Too bad they don't help light up the entire room...
How silly!
He exploded when I stomped him! Fortunately, the first few frames of an explosion don't harm the player for some reason.
Alright, seriously, how did I not get burned right there? I'm doing some slow-motion instant replays of that one!
Whoa, almost got a bullet up my butt while trying to redirect Blatzy's aim there.
I'm curious if there is something to the right here, perhaps reachable by spin jumping off of a mace, but I'm not gonna risk it.
Yeah, I'm running.
Got lucky with that one, and fortunately, those Birdos are burnable. Also, I'm guessing that the flames there act like lava, judging by the Podoboos leaping from them.
BGM: Kirby Super Star - Save Area (The Great Cave Offensive)
To be continued... Yo!
Oh, hey there Bigeye. How's it going?
Oh, man. It's one of those fly zones where I'm a 1HP wonder anyway, so my power up status wouldn't have mattered here anyway.
Thanks, I'll keep that hint in mind.
So, I guess this series of levels will have me rematching past bosses, but made more difficult by the terrain, right?
Oh, no. There's another one.
Ya, ya, ya! Get out of there!
Oh, god. I believe that pink koopa is an elite koopa, which I've seen in a few other hacks. They're really nasty, and take multiple stomps to defeat. It might be better to just avoid them altogether.
Yep, that's definitely lava, which burned up that gold statue. Am I supposed to Podoboo-bounce across these flames? Or can I maybe use the Boo instead?
Oh, come on! Why did I get hit there when I damaged him with my stomp as well? I hate things like that.
This one likes to spew out fireballs like a sprinkler, and causes a stunning quake when he lands.
Whoa! We begin on a wild ride while listening to one of the best songs in existence!
Huh. It appears that I sometimes lose my momentum as I warp to the other side of the screen. Does that happen going the other way? ...Yep. Alright, enough fooling around. I'm outta here!
Those were some tight dodges right there. That Boo coming at me from behind really complicated things.
Aw, I was hoping to pull off a 1-up combo using those Ninjis, but instead... Lava Lotus.

Whoa, those firebars are certainly hyped, perhaps for Twitch Plays Pok√©mon Blaze Black 2, starting in a couple of days? Oh, and supposedly a "force evolution" code will be used this time, so the B-trolls won't be able to do their usual thing!
Huh, what's this? Some flying 1-ups, a goal sphere, and two message boxes...
That many, apparently. (It took a total of 16 hits.)
...What the heck? Are Luigi's overalls flame-retardant all of a sudden? That fireball really looked like it should've scorched me! But, whatever!
Well, I'd've ended the video here, but it's been less than five minutes so far, so let's check out Else Castle 1 right now!

That Shotzo's placement is tricky, but I can still totally get past it. (Actually, these things are the "Blatzy" enemies from Kirby's Dream Land's Extra mode and Kirby Super Star Ultra's Revenge of the King mode, which I didn't notice until TheGoomba98 pointed it out, so pretend I said "Blatzy" instead of "Shotzo" earlier.)
I think I'll just hang out over here instead of trying to chase the guy. At least he isn't tossing projectiles or causing earthquakes with his jumps or anything like that.
Uh, oh. No Boo to use here (unless I count the one behind me, but I doubt I could make that Boo useful here)...
Testing now... And it still appears to be saving properly at this moment. I'd better keep paying close attention, though.
Whoa, what are these little things? Well, they're not harmful to me, nor am I able to harm them...
Whoa, holy helix!
Looks like the platforms here are spelling out something, literally.
Let's-a-go!
And there's a football Chuck... Wait, that didn't quite look like a football...
Nuts... I wasn't prepared for that hidden 1-up cake there, but at least the block didn't cause me to fall.
Keeping the guy just off screen messes with his fireball attack at least.
Somehow, I didn't get burned there! Also, from what I can tell, my fireballs just go through the pink duder without hitting him.
BGM: Touhou 6 - Remilia's Theme - Septette for the Dead Queen/Princess/Whatever
Oh, I bet they're actually the Yoshi's House bird sprites.
Zwee! Ooh, more cake! But, I don't need it right now.

The Shotzos do try to aim at me, but they can only fire in five distinct directions, so there's plenty of safe spots in between their firing lines (and underneath them), and it's possible to get them to fire in a direction where the bullets won't get in my way.
Fortunately for me, Blatzy's an idiot here! I think it might've been able to hit me there if it fired up-left instead of straight up there.
Swing and a miss! One more strike and I'm out! (However, I'm still upset about that first strike that the umpire called on me...)

...Oh, god, no... I forgot to make sure WMM saved the movie file correctly there before uploading this video... And, now I'm already over nine minutes in, and I don't want to reupload and reannotate everything up to this point... (Sure, when the annotation editor's saving ability doesn't malfunction while I'm paying attention for that, something else unexpectedly goes wrong...)
Oh, hey there red koopduder-- WHOA!!!
Huh. That quake didn't stun me for some reason.
Ooh, I managed to kill that one with two spin jump stomps! I don't know if spin jumping was actually necessary, but whatever.
He does not want to give me an opening, that's for sure!
Geez, how many hits does this guy take?
At least I probably won't ever have to go against the flow of the gigaspeed firebars... hopefully.
Oh, man. This triple-decker obstacle looks really tricky...
Any secrets up here? You never know...
Anything further to the right? Probably not.
Well, combining a Podoboo with the Boo worked.
Huh. This room wraps around horizontally, but is there any real reason for this? Well, I could run forever... Wheeeeee!!!

Okay, I can spin jump on these explosive koopas without them blowing up, so that's what I'm gonna do from now on. (Also, just like with Rexes, I get an upward bounce when I spin jump on them, unlike most enemies.)
There's a gold statue to go with the silver ones. Sure, why not?
This guy's not dead yet? Also, he's getting pretty fast... So, I guess the bosses themselves will be upgraded as well.
Yeah, I guess I'm kind of happy... maybe. It'll depend on how good the next four levels are.
Alright, now we've got undead duders and fire.
